<!-- HOW IT WORKS -->
<section class="section">
<h2><i class="fa-solid fa-circle-info"></i> How It Works</h2>

<p>
This platform is a mobile-first media processing system designed to analyze and process publicly accessible media streams efficiently. The application combines server-side processing with browser-based controls to provide a smooth workflow from URL input to final download.
</p>

<h3>1. URL Submission</h3>
<p>
Users provide a valid media link through the homepage. The system validates the structure of the URL and ensures it belongs to a supported source before any processing begins.
</p>

<h3>2. Metadata Extraction</h3>
<p>
After validation, the server retrieves structured information about the media. This includes title, thumbnail, duration, available formats, and quality levels. At this stage no media file is downloaded — only information is retrieved.
</p>

<h3>3. Format Selection</h3>
<p>
Users can choose a specific format such as video with audio, audio-only, or optimized formats for mobile devices. The available options depend entirely on the original media source.
</p>

<h3>4. Media Processing</h3>
<p>
The server processes the selected format. This may include merging video and audio streams, converting formats, extracting audio, or optimizing playback compatibility across devices.
</p>

<h3>5. Download Delivery</h3>
<p>
After processing completes, the generated file is delivered securely to the user's device. Temporary processing data may be automatically removed to preserve system storage.
</p>

<h3>6. Optional Features</h3>
<ul>
<li>Account-based download history</li>
<li>Playlist batch processing</li>
<li>Media conversion uploads</li>
<li>Progress tracking for large media</li>
<li>Cookie-based access for authorized private content</li>
</ul>
</section>

